{
  "_id": "lotmAbilityR9002",
  "name": "Indexed Safeguard",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "icons/magic/perception/eye-ringed-blue.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Baseline (0 Spirituality):</strong> As a bonus action, establish a disciplined mental index for 10 minutes (concentration). While active, you gain advantage on Arcana, History, and Investigation checks made to recall, categorize, or cross-reference information; gain a <strong>+1</strong> bonus to saving throws against charm, fear, and illusion effects; and once per short rest when preparing a ritual, reduce one preparation step by 1 minute (minimum 1 minute).</p><p><strong>Higher Spend (upcast):</strong></p><ul><li><strong>+1 Spirituality:</strong> Duration becomes 1 hour. Choose one ally within 30 feet; while the ally remains within 30 feet of you, they gain the baseline recall/cross-reference advantage.</li><li><strong>+2 Spirituality:</strong> Once while active, when you fail an Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma saving throw, you may reroll it (must use new result).</li><li><strong>+4 Spirituality:</strong> If you complete a ritual while this is active, reduce that ritual's spirituality surcharge by 1 (minimum 0) and ignore one nonmagical interruption that would normally force ritual re-setup.</li></ul><p><em>Counterplay:</em> Silence, sensory overload, or anti-magic suppression can break concentration and end the index early.</p><p><em>Corruption Hook:</em> If you knowingly endanger bystanders to protect a ritual optimization from this ability, gain 1 Corruption.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
